        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 5:37AM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 537 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Burns Junction to near Scott Reservoir.
Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Crooked Creek State Park, Scott Reservoir, and Burns Junction
around 640 AM MDT.
Rome and Round Mountain around 650 AM MDT.
Arock and Owyhee Butte around 700 AM MDT.
Danner and Iron Point around 720 AM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
